<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-09-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                    <head>No. 47.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Che
                                    Foo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-09-11"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 11, 1876</date>.
                            (Received November 7.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Just as the mail is closing I learn that the
                        British minister has closed his negotiation. The indemnity to be paid by the
                        Chinese is fixed at 200,000 taels.</p>
                    <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>GEORGE F. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                </div>
            </body></text></TEI>